    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> September 1, 2025</p>

    <p>BirdieBoard respects your privacy. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Name and email address (if you sign in)</li>
        <li>Optional profile photos</li>
        <li>Golf scores and game records</li>
        <li>Device information (for security purposes via Firebase AppCheck)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>To manage your user account and player profile</li>
        <li>To track scores, handicaps, and tournament results</li>
        <li>To protect access and detect fraud using Firebase AppCheck</li>
        <li>To improve performance using anonymized analytics (Firebase Analytics)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal data. Your data may be processed and stored by trusted third-party services, such as Firebase (by Google), used for authentication, cloud storage, and app security.</p>

    <h2>4. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You may request the deletion of your account or data at any time by contacting us at <a href="mailto:benbytecode@gmail.com">benbytecode@gmail.com</a>.</p>

    <h2>5. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions or concerns about this policy, please contact us at:</p>
    <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:benbytecode@gmail.com">benbytecode@gmail.com</a>
    </p>

    <p>Thank you for using BirdieBoard!</p>
